               <sex value="M" source="#bibl173-1">male</sex>
               <death when="0903" syriaca-computed-start="0903-01-01" source="#bibl173-1">0903</death>
               <note>Fiey provides the following bibliographic citations: <quote source="#bibl173-1">Sa vie : BHO, 779- 80. Ses ceuvres variees et multiples : Barsaum, Lu 'lu '2 , 434-41 ; J. Reller, M ose bar Kepha und seine Paulinenauslegung (Wiesbaden, 1994), 59- 76. Ses canons : Voobus, Sammlungen, 227. Son nom a ete ajoute en marge au texte de Rabban Saliba, le 12 fevrier. Le P. Peeters (Martyrologe, 175 n. 11) fait de Moise un patriarche, de meme que dans BHO, cit. BSO, II, 549 (J.M. Fiey).</quote>
               </note>
               <note type="abstract">Moses bar Kipha was a great scholar of the Syrian orthodox church.  He was a monk of the monastery of Saint Sergius near Balad.  He wrote on many topics and became a leader of the Metropolitan of Takrit, which was then vacant.</note>
